The paper deals with the normalization of citation data, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The use of statistical methods such as Mantel-Haenszel analysis and the focus on sparse data suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CY). Finally, the assessment of quality levels and the use of peer evaluations may also relate to social and information networks (cs.SI).
